text: Tried the dry Wanton Mee here. It‚Äôs pretty good. The char siew slices are burnt crispy, thick and it has both meat and fat which melts in your mouth when you chew. The noodles is springy, you can also taste the dry prawns in the chili which is nice but not spicy. The wantons are delicious and you get about 4 pieces compared to most stalls where you only get 2. Very underrated store.The evening staff looks angry all the time but he's actually very friendly and nice. What's even better is that the noodles and char siew is really good. This store deserve more customers.
Very good char siew and affordable. Noodles were cooked al-dente. Very recommended.
